  <h1>
   keyboard_virtual_status
  </h1>
  This function can be used to get the status of the virtual keyboard on the device running the game. The function will return
  <span>
   true
  </span>
  if the OS virtual keyboard is visible/being shown or
  <span>
   false
  </span>
  if it is hidden/hiding.
  <h4>
   Syntax
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">keyboard_virtual_status();
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Boolean
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">var _status = keyboard_virtual_status();
if _status == false
{
    keyboard_virtual_show(kbv_type_numbers, kbv_returnkey_default, kbv_autocapitalize_none, false);
}
</code></pre>
  The above code will show the OS virtual keyboard if the current status is
  <span>
   false
  </span>
  .
  <b>
  </b>
